 number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; Click this link for sample:&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>https://tinyurl.com/y928ma7p</u></p>\r\n<p><u>&nbsp;</u></p>\r\n<p><u>For new teachers who are new BPI EMV card users without the physical card.</u></p>\r\n<p>- Upload your recent deposit slip on the front and back part. Deposit slip must indicate the account number.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; Click this link for sample:&nbsp;<u>https://tinyurl.com/yb96ccej</u></p>\r\n<p><u>&nbsp;</u></p>\r\n<p><u><strong>For tenured teachers with existing BPI account,&nbsp;</strong></u></p>\r\n<p>- No need to update your bank information in Mypage.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For any request in changing or updating teacher&rsquo;s bank account, kindly send the following requirements to Fees Team using Support Portal:</p>\r\n<p>1. Completed Request letter (Letter - bank change -HBT.pdf)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Must be signed by the HBT above printed name</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Must be returned in PDF Format</p>\r\n<p>2. Copy of ID with signature</p>\r\n<p>3. Copy of Machine-validated bank receipt</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Must be clear and readable</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Should reflect the teacher&rsquo;s name and bank account number</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Deposit slip is acceptable</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; - Withdrawal slip is unacceptable</p>\r\n<p>4. Picture of ATM (front and Back) and Government issued ID</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Download 51Talk&rsquo;s template for change or update of your account details &ndash;&nbsp;<u>https://tinyurl.com/yblv4hr4</u></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Always upload your accurate bank account information in Account Settings via Mypage. Don&rsquo;t forget to double &ndash; check before clicking the &ldquo;Submit&rdquo; button.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For any concerns, create a ticket in Support Portal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let us know what you think of this announcement by taking our 1 minute survey through this link -&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://tinyurl.com/y77fzmht\">https://tinyurl.com/y77fzmht</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thank you.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-06-27 20:56:49','2018-06-27 22:47:55'),(206,'','AC Course List Issues ONGOING- Penalties will be reversed','2018-06-21','Phoebe Valencia','<p>Hi teachers,</p>\r\n<p>Your Lesson Support team is currently receiving high volume of contacts due to AC no schedule through this portal. Please expect your wait time to be longer as we are working on accommodating all your concerns.</p>\r\n<p><em>Do not conduct your lesson/s using any other platform (Skype/QQ) as it will not be honored.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Do not raise/send in a dispute right away because the issue is still on going.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>No need to contact our Technical Help Desk Department - This is a known and reported issue.</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</em><br /><br /><strong>All&nbsp;lesson&nbsp;penalties&nbsp;tied&nbsp;up&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;recent&nbsp;issue&nbsp;will be reversed.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>Sincerely,<br />51Talk Lesson Support</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-21 05:07:55','2018-06-21 07:38:56'),(216,'','PLEASE READ: AC NO RESERVATION DETAILS TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS','2018-06-25','Noel Clemente','<p><strong>PLEASE READ: AC NO RESERVATION DETAILS TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Posted on&nbsp;</strong><strong>June 25, 2018</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hi Teachers!</p>\r\n<p>Support is currently receiving volumes of calls and chats similar to what you are reporting:&nbsp;<strong><u>AC related Issue | AC No Reservation Details Data.</u></strong><br /> <br /> 51Talk is currently investigating this issue and will provide an update soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em><u>PLEASE TRY THE PROCEDURES BELOW BEFORE REPORTING TO US AS THIS MIGHT RESOLVE THE ISSUE:</u></em></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Use the AC Backup Classroom<br /> 2. Please click Menu &gt; System Setting &gt; Clean.&nbsp;<br /> 3.Then it will prompt to reboot, please select Yes.&nbsp;<br /> 4. Finally, login again to AC to see if this will resolve the issue</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em><u>NOTE:&nbsp; IF NONE OF THE BASIC TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS WORKED, YOU MIGHT NEED FURTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. PLEASE CONTACT OUR TECH TEAM BY USING THE \"TECH BUBBLE\" ON THE LIVE CHAT OPTIONS BELOW!</u></em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-06-25 04:12:50','2018-06-25 04:12:50'),(210,'','AC OUTAGE - No Reservation Details Data','2018-06-23','Rodj Casin','<p>Hi&nbsp;Teachers!<br /><br />Support&nbsp;is&nbsp;currently&nbsp;receiving&nbsp;volumes&nbsp;of&nbsp;calls&nbsp;and&nbsp;chats&nbsp;affecting&nbsp;teachers&nbsp;similar&nbsp;to&nbsp;what&nbsp;you&nbsp;are&nbsp;reporting :AC related Issue | <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>AC OUTAGE - No Reservation Details Data</strong></span>.&nbsp;<br /><br />51Talk&nbsp;is&nbsp;currently&nbsp;investigating this&nbsp;issue&nbsp;and&nbsp;will&nbsp;provide&nbsp;an&nbsp;update&nbsp;shortly.<br /><br />All&nbsp;lesson&nbsp;penalties&nbsp;tied&nbsp;up&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;recent&nbsp;issue&nbsp;would&nbsp;be&nbsp;reviewed&nbsp;for&nbsp;reversal.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>NOTE:</strong></span><br />*Do not conduct your lesson/s using any other platform (Skype/QQ) as it will not be honored.</p>\r\n<p>*Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.</p>\r\n<p>*Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.</p>\r\n<p>*Do not raise/send in a dispute right away because the issue is still on going.</p>\r\n<p>*No need to contact TECH for validation.</p>\r\n<p>*No need to follow up, everyone is affected.</p>\r\n<p>*Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>PLEASE TRY DOING THESE FIRST:</strong></span><br />*System&nbsp;Setting&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<br />Clean&gt; Then&nbsp;it&nbsp;will&nbsp;prompt&nbsp;to&nbsp;reboot,&nbsp;please&nbsp;select&nbsp;Yes&gt;<br />Finally,&nbsp;login&nbsp;again&nbsp;to&nbsp;AC<br /><br />*Clear Cahce&gt; Exit AC&gt; Close AC App&gt; Re-launch AC App&gt; Re-log<br /><br /><br />Thanks&nbsp;for&nbsp;your&nbsp;patience&nbsp;and&nbsp;understanding.</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-23 06:09:12','2018-06-23 06:45:54'),(208,'','AC Issue Course List Fixed-Please log in to AC now','2018-06-21','Phoebe Valencia','<p>Hi teachers,</p>\r\n<p>AC Course List Issue has been fixed.</p>\r\n<p>All&nbsp;lesson&nbsp;penalties&nbsp;tied&nbsp;up&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;recent&nbsp;issue&nbsp;will be&nbsp;reversed.</p>\r\n<p>No need to submit a dispute validation ticket for this outage nor report this to your Technical or Lesson Support Team.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Affected lessons&nbsp;06/21/2018: 20:00, 20:30, 21:00, 21:30,22:00</strong></p>\r\n<p>Note:</p>\r\n<p>Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.</p>\r\n<p>Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.</p>\r\n<p>Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks&nbsp;for&nbsp;your&nbsp;patience&nbsp;and&nbsp;understanding.</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-21 08:09:17','2018-06-21 08:32:53'),(209,'','Penalties will be reversed on AC Issue Course List Fixed-June 21, 2018','2018-06-22','Zel Redillas','<p>Hi teachers,</p>\r\n<p>AC Course List Issue has been fixed, yesterday- June 21, 2018</p>\r\n<p>All&nbsp;lesson&nbsp;penalties&nbsp;tied&nbsp;up&nbsp;with&nbsp;the&nbsp;recent&nbsp;issue&nbsp;will be&nbsp;reversed.</p>\r\n<p>No need to submit a dispute validation ticket for this outage nor report this to your Technical or Lesson Support Team.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Affected lessons&nbsp;06/21/2018: 20:00, 20:30, 21:00, 21:30,22:00</strong></p>\r\n<p>Note:</p>\r\n<p>Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.</p>\r\n<p>Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.</p>\r\n<p>Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</p>\r\n<p>Thanks&nbsp;for&nbsp;your&nbsp;patience&nbsp;and&nbsp;understanding.</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-21 20:35:49','2018-06-21 21:51:54'),(229,'','AC AUDIO CHANNEL','2018-06-30','Rodj Casin','<p>Hi All,<br /><br />For those who are experiencing issues with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>\"AC AUDIO CHANNEL\"</strong></span>, please inform your student that both of you need to exit and re-enter the AC Classroom for this to work.<br /><br />if exiting &amp; re-entering the classroom doesn\'t work, kindly take and save screenshots of the error &amp; run an updated speedtest to serve as proof if in case you might need to file a dispute because of this problem.<br /><br />If you might need further technical assistance, please contact our Tech Team by using the \"Tech Bubble\".<br /><br /><br />NOTE:&nbsp;<br />*Do not conduct your lesson/s using any other platform (Skype/QQ) as it will not be honored.<br />*Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.<br />*Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.<br />*Do not raise/send in a dispute right away, have Tech Team validate it first and move on from there.<br /><br />Thanks for your cooperation!<br /><br /></p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-30 07:04:26','2018-06-30 09:26:34'),(214,'','AC NO RESERVATION DETAILS TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS','2018-06-25','JP Gorospe','<p>Hi Teachers!</p>\r\n<p>Support is currently receiving volumes of calls and chats similar to what you are reporting :AC related Issue | AC No Reservation Details Data.<br /><br />51Talk is currently investigating this issue and will provide an update shortly.</p>\r\n<p>PLEASE TRY THE PROCEDURES BELOW AS THIS MIGHT RESOLVE THE ISSUE:</p>\r\n<p>1. Use the AC Backup Classroom<br />2. Please click Menu &gt; System Setting &gt; Clean.&nbsp;<br />3.Then it will prompt to reboot, please select Yes.&nbsp;<br />4. Finally, login again to AC to see if this will resolve the issue</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-23 18:55:47','2018-06-25 04:13:04'),(227,'','AC NO RESERVATION DETAILS TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS','2018-06-30','JP Gorospe','<p>Hi Teachers!</p>\r\n<p>Support is currently receiving volumes of calls and chats similar to what you are reporting: <strong>AC related Issue | AC No Reservation Details Data.</strong><br /> <br />51Talk is currently investigating this issue and will provide an update soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>PLEASE TRY THE PROCEDURES BELOW BEFORE REPORTING TO US AS THIS MIGHT RESOLVE THE ISSUE:</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>1. Use the AC Backup Classroom<br />2. Please click Menu &gt; System Setting &gt; Clean. <br />3.Then it will prompt to reboot, please select Yes. <br />4. Finally, login again to AC to see if this will resolve the issue</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>NOTE:&nbsp; IF NONE OF THE BASIC TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS WORKED, YOU MIGHT NEED FURTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. PLEASE CONTACT OUR TECH TEAM BY USING THE \"TECH BUBBLE\" ON THE LIVE CHAT OPTIONS BELOW!</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-06-29 19:45:54','2018-06-29 21:21:42'),(230,'','Reversal and  Full Payment for the Lessons Affected by System Issue- June 30, 2018','2018-07-01','Zel Redillas','<p><em><strong>PHBEE Operational Update - June 30, 2018(2018-07-01 19:11:30)</strong></em><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>Hi, teachers!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Reversals and full payment for the lessons (base lesson rate) affected by the system issue on <strong>June 30, 2018</strong> has been processed for the following intervals - <strong>21:00, 21:30, 22:00 and 22:30</strong>. (<em>This does not include K-12 and weekend incentive as it is applicable for ended lessons only and student\'s absence is still half pay.)!&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>Lesson Fee supplementation details can be seen on the<strong> &ldquo;Others&rdquo;</strong> section of your<strong> Lesson Fee Summary</strong>. Absence count and penalties have been removed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For isolated cases, you may file a dispute by submitting a ticket with corresponding proofs and screenshots via the<strong> Support Portal - http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thank you very much for your usual support and cooperation.</p>\r\n<p>Continue to open your slots as there are plenty of students waiting to have FUN and engaging lessons with you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>51Talk&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-07-01 04:21:07','2018-07-01 04:21:07'),(231,'','AC ISSUE - PLEASE CHECK THE TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS','2018-07-02','Rodj Casin','<p>Hi Teachers!</p>\r\n<p>Support is currently receiving high volume of <em><strong>calls</strong></em> and <em><strong>chats</strong></em> similar to what you are reporting: <strong>AC related Issue</strong></p>\r\n<p>51Talk is currently investigating this issue and will provide an update soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>PLEASE TRY THE PROCEDURES BELOW BEFORE REPORTING TO US AS THIS MIGHT RESOLVE THE ISSUE:</strong></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Clear Cache</em></li>\r\n<li><em>(Settings) Do an Equipment Test (Online)</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Exit AC Application</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Re-log in into the AC Application</em></li>\r\n<li><em>If courselist is not appearing &gt; Entry \"back Up Classroom\"&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em><strong>NOTE:&nbsp; <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">IF NONE OF THE BASIC TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS WORKED, YOU MIGHT NEED FURTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. PLEASE CONTACT OUR TECH TEAM BY USING THE \"TECH BUBBLE\" ON THE LIVE CHAT OPTIONS BELOW!</span></strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>*Do not conduct your lesson/s using any other platform (Skype/QQ) as it will not be honored.<br />*Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">unable to conduct</span>.<br />*Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.<br />*Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Outage','Resolve','2018-07-01 06:16:08','2018-07-02 08:56:34'),(232,'','2-Level Guaranteed Earnings','2018-07-02','Rodj Casin','<p>Welcome to 51Talk, teachers!</p>\r\n<p>July New Teacher Guaranteed Earnings is on for new teachers launched starting July 1, 2018 until July 15, 2018! Open peak slots and take advantage of the Guaranteed Earnings!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>How to Qualify:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Open 65 peak slots and not have more than 2 missed lessons per full cutoff to earn 3,000Php if earnings is under 3,000Php.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Open 90 or more peak slots and not have more than 2 missed lessons per full cutoff to earn 4,000Php if earnings is under 4,000Php.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Take note, peak slots are at 1900-2130 on weekdays and 9am to 2130 on weekends.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Teachers launched from July 1, 2018 until July 15, 2018! are qualified. All new teachers launched within the specified dates would enjoy the guaranteed pay incentive until August 31, 2018!</p>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>Lessons with attendance issues like absences, late and leave early will not be counted.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Student absent is not considered as a successful lesson.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>*Please be advised that Guaranteed Earning would not be on top of your pay.&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s the season to teach with 51talk!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s have a productive month and earn more!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thank you!</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-07-02 03:54:46','2018-07-02 03:54:46'),(233,'','AC ISSUE - PLEASE CHECK THE TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS','2018-07-02','Rodj Casin','<p>Hi Teachers!</p>\r\n<p>Support is currently receiving high volume of <em><strong>calls</strong></em> and <em><strong>chats</strong></em> similar to what you are reporting: <strong>AC related Issue</strong></p>\r\n<p>51Talk is currently investigating this issue and will provide an update soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>PLEASE TRY THE PROCEDURES BELOW BEFORE REPORTING TO US AS THIS MIGHT RESOLVE THE ISSUE:</strong></em></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Clear Cache</em></li>\r\n<li><em>(Settings) Do an Equipment Test (Online)</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Exit AC Application</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Re-log in into the AC Application</em></li>\r\n<li><em>If courselist is not appearing &gt; Entry \"back Up Classroom\"&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em><strong>NOTE:&nbsp; IF NONE OF THE BASIC TROUBLESHOOTING STEPS WORKED, YOU MIGHT NEED FURTHER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. PLEASE CONTACT OUR TECH TEAM BY USING THE \"TECH BUBBLE\" ON THE LIVE CHAT OPTIONS BELOW!</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em><strong>*Do not conduct your lesson/s using any other platform (Skype/QQ) as it will not be honored.<br />*Do not post Lesson Memo/s for lesson/s that you are unable to conduct.<br />*Do not tag the student as absent, leave the lesson as it is.<br />*Save screenshots of all the errors you\'ve encountered (for reference purposes).</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>Thanks for your patience and understanding.</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-07-02 06:30:55','2018-07-02 06:30:55'),(234,'','New Technical Helpdesk Support Landing Page','2018-07-03','Zel Redillas','<p>Awesome day, teacher!</p>\r\n<p>51Talk has provided a &ldquo;Self-Help&rdquo; page wherein PHBEE could initially check prior to contacting a Technical Support agent.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>Why is it helpful and important?</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to wait on queue! Just click the issue you are experiencing and follow the provided troubleshooting steps. In this way, Technical Helpdesk could support other PHBEEs who greatly need help.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>What&rsquo;s in the new landing page?</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>- Basic troubleshooting steps for common technical issues</p>\r\n<p>- Advisory of a known outage</p>\r\n<p>- Penalty Removal Request &ndash; This button will only pop-up when there&rsquo;s an AC outage. Click the button to secure a ticket number and PHBEEs will receive an automated reply.</p>\r\n<p>To know more about it, check this link &ndash;&nbsp;https://tinyurl.com/y8u6rtql&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The new landing page for Technical Helpdesk will go live on July 4, 2018.</p>\r\n<p>This is the perfect time to upgrade your technical skills by exploring the new page.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for the continuous support!</p>\r\n<p>51Talk</p>','Downtime Advisory','Active','2018-07-03 03:15:36','2018-07-03 03:16:26');
