ontent/uploads/2016/09/121.jpg 871w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/121-300x145.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/121-768x371.jpg 768w\" alt=\"121\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.&nbsp;Error Message 1</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-396\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/122.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/122.png 602w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/122-300x119.png 300w\" alt=\"122\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4.&nbsp;Error Message 2</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-397\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/123.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/123.jpg 488w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/123-300x198.jpg 300w\" alt=\"123\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5.&nbsp;Error Message 3</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-398\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/125.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/125.jpg 577w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/125-300x229.jpg 300w\" alt=\"125\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6.&nbsp;Adding contact error</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-399\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/126.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/126.jpg 620w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/126-300x208.jpg 300w\" alt=\"126\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7.&nbsp;Verification Error</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-400\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/127.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/127.jpg 657w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/127-300x159.jpg 300w\" alt=\"127\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">8.&nbsp;Contact Request Error</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-401\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/128.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/128.jpg 725w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/128-300x163.jpg 300w\" alt=\"128\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">9.&nbsp;Validation Question</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-402\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/129.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 747px) 100vw, 747px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/129.jpg 747w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/129-300x157.jpg 300w\" alt=\"129\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Note:&nbsp;For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:34:42','2017-08-02 05:31:25'),(10,2,4,'QQ Biz Manual','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Installation</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Click <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://dldir1.qq.com/qqfile/crm/hrtx/EIM_r78448.dmg\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">here</span></a> to download.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Logging In</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Step 1: Input your given QQ ID and Password.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Note: QQ Biz would usually start with the number 2.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-281\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/76.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 271px) 100vw, 271px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/76.jpg 271w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/76-236x300.jpg 236w\" alt=\"76\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>QQ Biz Functions</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-283\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/77.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 724px) 100vw, 724px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/77.jpg 724w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/77-300x208.jpg 300w\" alt=\"77\" /><br /></strong>1. Check Message &ndash; (Conversation bubble on the left side) enables you to view messages sent to you.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Nickname &ndash; (Preferably your Teacher&rsquo;s name) is your display name in QQ.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3. Audio call &ndash; (mic icon in the upper right corner of the app) enables you to call and do voice calls.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4. Video Call &ndash; (camera icon beside the audio call function) enables you to do video calls.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5. Send Files &ndash; (Folder icon beside the video call function) enables you to send files to your students or target user.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6. Emojis &ndash; (smiley icon above the chat box) enables you to send smileys.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7. Chat box &ndash; (boxed area at the bottom of the app) enables you to type in your messages</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Search for Existing Contacts<br /></strong>1. Click on the Search button (box with magnifying glass) on the upper left hand side of the console.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Once the cursor is on the box, type in the person that you&rsquo;ll search. You can search for:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">a. QQ ID (numbers)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">b. Display Name (Nickname)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-284\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/78.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/78.jpg 758w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/78-300x170.jpg 300w\" alt=\"78\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Adding Contacts<br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-285\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/79.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/79.jpg 660w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/79-300x190.jpg 300w\" alt=\"79\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Click on the messages icon (conversation bubble).</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Input the QQ ID of the student or contact that you want to add in the Search Box (boxed magnifying glass icon).</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3. Click the ADD CONTACT icon (Orange person with the plus sign).</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4. Click on the ADD button on the lower left side of the ADD CONTACT dialogue box.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5. On the ADD dialogue box you can input your message on the box so the student can recognize you (EX. Hi! I&rsquo;m teacher John, your 51talk teacher for today. Please add me up). You can create a categorization on the following box such as friends, students etc. and input their corresponding display name on your contacts (EX. Diane &ndash; Student, Ivy &ndash; KIDS Student)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:36:03','2017-08-02 05:29:16'),(11,3,0,'Audio and Video Settings','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1.&nbsp;Adjust Audio and Video Settings</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Tools on the Menu Bar then select Options</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-152\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/30.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 977px) 100vw, 977px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/30.jpg 977w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/30-300x145.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/30-768x370.jpg 768w\" alt=\"30\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2.&nbsp;Select headset as device for Skype</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Under General, click Audio Settings tab</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Select your headset on the drop down list on both Microphone and Speakers</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-153\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/31.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/31.jpg 786w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/31-300x230.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/31-768x588.jpg 768w\" alt=\"31\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Save if you&rsquo;re done.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.&nbsp;Check video</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Under General, click Video Settings</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Wait for your video to load.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/32.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/32.jpg 786w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/32-300x230.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/32-768x588.jpg 768w\" alt=\"32\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Save if you&rsquo;re done.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4. What to do if Video does not work</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Using external camera:</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Close video settings; re-plug your camera; then check video settings again.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*If still not loading, check if working on other apps.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*If not working on other app, webcam may be defective. Use another webcam.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Using internal camera:</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Check on other apps if video is loading.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*If not loading on other apps, have your computer checked by local technician.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Note: You may disable all other installed camera. Use this link on how to: <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/index.php/knowledge-base/pcinternet-optimization/disabling-other-webcam-installed/\">Disabling Other Webcam Installed</a></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5.&nbsp;Check audio and video</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Conduct echo test &ndash; search Echo/Sound Test Service then click the phone icon</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/33.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 976px) 100vw, 976px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/33.jpg 976w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/33-300x190.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/33-768x487.jpg 768w\" alt=\"33\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:37:47','2017-08-02 05:32:46'),(12,4,0,'Appearance Checker â€“ Choose default camera','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Too many webcams installed in your PC?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Set the webcam that you use on your appearance checker. Just follow these steps on how-to:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open camera settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on the camera icon on the appearance checker then select <strong>Settings<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-225\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 546px) 100vw, 546px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52.jpg 546w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/52-300x188.jpg 300w\" alt=\"52\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Adobe Flash Player Settings window</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the camera icon</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-226\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 422px) 100vw, 422px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53.jpg 422w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/53-300x209.jpg 300w\" alt=\"53\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Choose the camera that you want to use on the drop down list.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-227\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 432px) 100vw, 432px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54.jpg 432w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/54-300x212.jpg 300w\" alt=\"54\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Check if camera is working</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click on the camera thumbnail to check if your camera is working.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-228\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55.jpg 577w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/55-300x177.jpg 300w\" alt=\"55\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*If prompted, allow the website to access your camera by clicking Allow</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-229\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 364px) 100vw, 364px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56.jpg 364w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/56-300x114.jpg 300w\" alt=\"56\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*You should be able to see yourself on the thumbnail.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 276px) 100vw, 276px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57.jpg 276w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/57-231x300.jpg 231w\" alt=\"57\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click close then proceed with the appearance checker.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>Refer to this article on how-to: MyPage Appearance Checker</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page. We are online 08:00-22:30 Beijing Time (UTC+8:00)</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:42:05','2017-08-02 05:34:04'),(13,4,0,'My Booking Schedule Alignment Error','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Is your booking scheduled not aligned?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Adjust your browser&rsquo;s resolution.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;My booking schedule not aligned<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-264\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 685px) 100vw, 685px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67.jpg 685w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/67-300x235.jpg 300w\" alt=\"67\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Browser resolution may not be set to default (100%)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Adjust browser screen resolution</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Set browser resolution to default (100%)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Google Chrome</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the magnifying glass then click Set to Default button.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-265\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 657px) 100vw, 657px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68.jpg 657w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/68-300x103.jpg 300w\" alt=\"68\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Mozilla Firefox</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Open browser menu then adjust resolution to 100%</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-267\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70.jpg 549w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/70-300x125.jpg 300w\" alt=\"70\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:42:46','2017-08-02 05:34:45'),(14,4,0,'MyPage Appearance Checker','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Having trouble going through the Appearance Checker in MyPage?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Log-in to MyPage &ndash; <span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><a style=\"color: #3366ff;\" href=\"http://www.51talk.com/ph\">www.51talk.com/ph</a></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Click the <u>check appearance now</u> button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-251\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61.jpg 560w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/61-300x191.jpg 300w\" alt=\"61\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Allow MyPage to access your camera.<br />*Click the <u>Allow</u> button<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-252\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62.jpg 562w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/62-300x86.jpg 300w\" alt=\"62\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>4.&nbsp;Position yourself in front of your camera then click the capture button<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-253\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 382px) 100vw, 382px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63.jpg 382w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/63-300x268.jpg 300w\" alt=\"63\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">**Make sure to follow the proper guidelines:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-254\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64.jpg 399w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/64-271x300.jpg 271w\" alt=\"64\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>5.&nbsp;You should be prompted by a window that the image has been saved successfully. Then click the <u>OK&nbsp;</u>button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-255\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65.jpg 545w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/65-300x77.jpg 300w\" alt=\"65\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>6.&nbsp;Click the <u>Enter my page</u> button to enter your account.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-256\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66.jpg 560w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/66-300x201.jpg 300w\" alt=\"66\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>**Once you successfully upload/capture a photo but were still prompted to capture a photo, you may just click on Enter MyPage button (as long as you have successfully captured a photo).</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 00:59:56','2017-08-02 05:35:34'),(15,5,0,'Clear Cache and Cookies','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open browser history settings &ndash; Google Chrome</strong>&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-165\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 30px) 100vw, 30px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome.jpg 195w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/chrome-150x150.jpg 150w\" alt=\"chrome\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Customize and control Google Chrome button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-166\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35.jpg 428w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/35-300x86.jpg 300w\" alt=\"35\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Open History page</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-167\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 532px) 100vw, 532px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36.jpg 532w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/36-300x205.jpg 300w\" alt=\"36\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Clear browsing data button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-168\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37.jpg 889w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37-300x118.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/37-768x302.jpg 768w\" alt=\"37\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Place a check mark on all options. Choose &ldquo;the beginning of time&rdquo; on the drop down then click Clear browsing data button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-169\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38.jpg 504w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/38-300x259.jpg 300w\" alt=\"38\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Wait for the whole process to finish then reload your browser.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Open browser history settings &ndash; Mozilla Firefox&nbsp;<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-170\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/firefox.jpg\" alt=\"firefox\" width=\"28\" height=\"26\" /></strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Open menu button then click History</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-171\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39.jpg 421w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/39-250x300.jpg 250w\" alt=\"39\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Clear Recent History</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-172\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 285px) 100vw, 285px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40.jpg 285w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/40-152x300.jpg 152w\" alt=\"40\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Select &ldquo;Everything&rdquo; on the drop down. Place a check mark on the highlighted list then click Clear Now button.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-173\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 361px) 100vw, 361px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41.jpg 361w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/41-300x293.jpg 300w\" alt=\"41\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Wait for the whole process to finish then reload your browser.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:01:17','2017-08-02 05:36:24'),(16,5,0,'Disabling Other Webcam Installed','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;View installed webcam</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click start/windows button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Type Device Manager on the Search box then click Device Manager</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-187\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 336px) 100vw, 336px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42.jpg 336w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/42-195x300.jpg 195w\" alt=\"42\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Disable other installed camera device</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the arrow on Imaging devices</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on the camera device that you don&rsquo;t use then click Disable</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:</strong> The camera that you are currently using should be listed on the Imaging device. If not, re-plug or install your camera&rsquo;s driver.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-188\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 555px) 100vw, 555px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44.jpg 555w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/44-300x178.jpg 300w\" alt=\"44\" /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:01:53','2017-08-02 05:36:57'),(17,5,0,'How to Install Flash Player Active X','2017-06-05','<p><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">For Windows OS</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">1. Use <strong>Internet Explorer</strong> browser to open Adobe Flash Website.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Link:&nbsp;http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">2. Click&nbsp;on &ldquo;Need Flash Player for a different computer?&rdquo; link.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-338\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1002px) 100vw, 1002px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101.jpg 1002w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101-300x181.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/101-768x462.jpg 768w\" alt=\"101\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">3.&nbsp;For &ldquo;Step 1&rdquo; select the Operating System that corresponds to your computer&rsquo;s Operating System (ex. Windows 7)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-340\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1004px) 100vw, 1004px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103.jpg 1004w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/103-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"103\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">4.&nbsp;For &ldquo;Step 2&rdquo; select &ldquo;FP for Internet Explorer &ndash; Active X&rdquo;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-341\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1005px) 100vw, 1005px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104.jpg 1005w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/104-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"104\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">5. Uncheck all box under Optional Offers</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-342\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1005px) 100vw, 1005px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105.jpg 1005w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/105-768x420.jpg 768w\" alt=\"105\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">6. Click the <strong>Download now</strong> button</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-343\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1006px) 100vw, 1006px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106.jpg 1006w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106-300x164.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/106-768x419.jpg 768w\" alt=\"106\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">7. Wait for the process to finish</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-348\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107.jpg 713w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/107-300x181.jpg 300w\" alt=\"107\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">8.&nbsp;If this yellow bar appear below, just click on &ldquo;Save&rdquo;</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-349\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108.jpg 713w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/108-300x199.jpg 300w\" alt=\"108\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">9.&nbsp;Once download is complete you will see the white bar below then just click &ldquo;Open Folder&rdquo; to see the installer that you have downloaded.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-350\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 718px) 100vw, 718px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109.jpg 718w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/109-300x201.jpg 300w\" alt=\"109\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">10. Open the file to install</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-351\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110.jpg 716w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/110-300x113.jpg 300w\" alt=\"110\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">11.&nbsp;If there is a prompt that asks if you want to install updates for adobe flash, just select &ldquo;Allow updates&hellip;.(Recommended) then click &ldquo;Next&rdquo;.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*Wait for the process to finish<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-352\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 787px) 100vw, 787px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111.jpg 787w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111-300x184.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/111-768x471.jpg 768w\" alt=\"111\" /><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:03:24','2017-08-02 05:39:42'),(18,5,0,'Set your headset as your default device','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Having audio issues on your teaching apps?</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Try to set your headset as the default device of your PC.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;View installed devices.</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click the volume icon on your taskbar (usually beside the time/date of your PC)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click Playback devices</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-214\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/51.jpg\" alt=\"51\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;Set your headset as default Playback Device (Audio)</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Right-click on your headset then click Set as Default Device</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>Note:</em></strong><em> Also set your headset as the Default Communication Device.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-235\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 563px) 100vw, 563px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58.jpg 563w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/58-300x251.jpg 300w\" alt=\"58\" /><br />*<strong>Note:</strong> After setting your headset as the default device, there should be a green indicator with a check mark on your headset.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-236\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/59.jpg\" alt=\"59\" /><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Set your headset as default Recording Device (Microphone)</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Go to Recording tab on the Sounds window. Right-click on your headset and click Set as Default Device.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><em>Note:</em></strong><em> Also set your headset as the Default Communication Device.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-237\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60.jpg 599w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/60-300x232.jpg 300w\" alt=\"60\" /></em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>*Click Apply (if possible) then Click OK<br /></em></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:05:00','2017-08-02 05:40:39'),(19,5,0,'Setting proxy on your browser','2017-06-05','<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Workaround to access MyPage using Google Chrome</span><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Disclaimer</strong><strong>:</strong> Once the proxy was set, you can only access the 51talk website. Other websites will be inaccessible. If you will access other websites. You may just simply uncheck the check box for proxy server.</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>1.&nbsp;Open your browser</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click the <strong>Customize and control Google Chrome</strong> button.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Click settings</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1008px) 100vw, 1008px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1.jpg 1008w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1-300x148.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/45-1-768x378.jpg 768w\" alt=\"45\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>2.&nbsp;On the search bar, type &ldquo;proxy&rdquo;<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-200\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1001px) 100vw, 1001px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1.jpg 1001w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1-300x187.jpg 300w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/46-1-768x480.jpg 768w\" alt=\"46\" /><br /></strong>*Then click the Change proxy settings button.<strong><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>3.&nbsp;Click the LAN Settings button.<br /><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 363px) 100vw, 363px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47.jpg 363w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/47-236x300.jpg 236w\" alt=\"47\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>4.&nbsp;Local Area Network (LAN) Settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Check <strong>Automatically detect settings </strong>under Automatic configuration.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Check the following under Proxy server:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&ndash;&nbsp;Use a proxy server for your LAN (These settings will not apply to dial-up or VPN connections).</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&ndash; Bypass proxy server for local addressess</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Then enter the following details under Proxy server:</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Address:</strong> 116.213.69.32</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Port:</strong> 80</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 405px) 100vw, 405px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48.jpg 405w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/48-300x262.jpg 300w\" alt=\"48\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>5.&nbsp;Disabling Proxy settings</strong></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">*Un-check <strong>Use a proxy server for your LAN&hellip;..</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-203\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" srcset=\"http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49.jpg 402w, http://116.93.119.130/support/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/49-300x263.jpg 300w\" alt=\"49\" /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>For technical assistance, contact your Tech Support Admins &ndash; click the chat button at the bottom of this page.</em></span></p>','2017-06-05 01:06:42','2017-08-02 05:41:22'),(20,6,0,'Network Troubleshooting Basics: Some Simple Steps','2017-06-05','<div class=\"post-meta\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span class=\"small\">by</span> <span class=\"author vcard\"><span class=\"fn\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" title=\"Posts by Ryan D. Lang\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/author/ryandla/\" rel=\"author\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">Ryan D. Lang</a></span></span> <span class=\"small\">on</span><span class=\"post-date updated\"> <abbr class=\"date time published\" title=\"2011-05-30T12:38:13+0200\">May 30, 2011</abbr> </span><span class=\"small\">in</span> <span class=\"categories\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/category/networks/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">Network</a></span> &ndash; Last Update:<span class=\"post_date date updated\"><abbr title=\"2015-01-29T19:23:24+0200\">January 29, 2015</abbr></span><span class=\"post-comments comments\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/30/network-troubleshooting-basics-some-simple-steps/#comments\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">&nbsp;</a></span></span></div>\r\n<div class=\"post-meta\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<section class=\"entry\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This article is the fourth and final part of a series on the basics of network troubleshooting. The tools covered in the previous articles (<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/12/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ping-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ping</a>, <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/17/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ipconfig-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ipconfig</a>, <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/24/network-troubleshooting-basics-tracert-pathping/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">tracert and pathping</a>) will be combined into a troubleshooting method. This guide will teach you valuable steps in finding where a problem is on a network connection.</span>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Knowing these commands before having to deal with the frustration of a network connection problem is not a bad idea. A working connection shows you what is supposed to happen. If you see something different, you will know something is up. When problems strike, at the least you can get an idea of what is going on.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 0: Check the Cords &amp; Power</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The first thing you should always do is check to make sure everything is plugged in: your computer, router, device, etc. Many laptops have a button to turn off the wireless connection; the icon looks like a signal tower. When in doubt, read the manual (which you can often download from the manufacturer&rsquo;s website). Bear in mind, we all forget this step at some point, so do not feel too silly when it happens to you.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 1: Ping Yourself</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You want to test that your machine is working properly. To do this, you want to ping yourself. You use the loop-back address (127.0.0.1) to do this. Pinging the loop-back address tests to make sure software on your computer is working properly. Typically, if something is not working at this stage, you may just need to restart your computer.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">ping</span></p>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"&ldquo;Network Troubleshooting Basics: The Ping Command&rdquo; &mdash; gHacks Technology News\" src=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/12/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ping-command/embed/#?secret=9pypesYRT2\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" data-secret=\"9pypesYRT2\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 2: Ping Your Router (AKA: the Default Gateway)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The next step would be to ping your router. You can find your router&rsquo;s IP address with ipconfig as well (it should be on the bottom of the unit and listed in the manual too). Remember that <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/05/17/network-troubleshooting-basics-the-ipconfig-command/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">ipconfig</a> lists your router as the &ldquo;Default Gateway.&rdquo; It is very likely to be <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/04/29/why-your-home-router-is-192-168-1-1/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">192.168.1.1</a> or a similar number.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This is done to test if your router is responding. If it is not, and you have already checked to make sure it is on, then it may need to be turned off and turned on. Every once in a while it may need a refresh. If the problem continues, contact you ISP for assistance to see if they can help.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Note: Routers, like anything else in the IT world, will someday fail. There is a chance that this has happened. Your ISP help desk should be able to help you determine this. If the router is one of theirs, they will likely send you out a new one.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 3: Ping Yourself with Your IP Address</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">We want to test to make sure everything is working correctly between your router and your computer. To do this, ping your IP address. It is listed in the ipconfig command at the same time the router IP number is. If this works, you can be pretty confident that a problem is outside your home (or maybe small office) network.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step 4: Ping and Tracert Outside Your Network</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-109540     lazyloaded\" style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\" srcset=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg 677w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-660x404.jpg 660w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-100x61.jpg 100w\" alt=\"network trace\" data-lazy-src=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg\" data-lazy-srcset=\"http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace.jpg 677w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-660x404.jpg 660w, http://cdn.ghacks.net/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/network-trace-100x61.jpg 100w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\" /></a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From here, you want to test something outside your network. In a medium or larger network setting, a server on another branch of the network will do. For a home network, the Internet is often your only option. Since chances are the problem is that one or more websites are (or seem) down, this is a logical thing to check.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You can use a few different tools. First try the ping command because it is the fastest. It will only tell you if the site is working or not. For more detailed information, use tracert and pathping. They can give a better idea of what is going on. For instance, if you can reach your router, but no further, the node that connects you to the Internet may be down: an ISP issue. If you can reach only a couple (one or two) steps past your router, then it still is probably an ISP issue. Your Internet is down. If you can reach a lot further, the site may be having issues (see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2011/02/17/is-facebook-down-find-out-right-now/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">is Facebook down</a>, ways to <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.ghacks.net/2008/03/16/ways-to-check-if-a-website-is-really-down/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">check if a website is really down</a>, for pointers) There even is a chance that other sites, either from the same proximity or even hosting service, are having the same problem. If it is an e-commerce site, there may be a number to call, but there probably is not much to do besides wait. At least you know where the problem is.</span></p>\r\n</section>','2017-06-05 01:10:32','2017-08-02 05:47:16'),(22,8,0,'How do I install Adobe Acrobat DC for Windows?','2017-06-05','<div class=\"page-description\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow the instructions below to download and install Adobe Acrobat Reader DC on Windows.</span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_5\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Mac users</strong>: If you&rsquo;re running Mac OS, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-mac-os.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install Adobe Acrobat Reader DC on Mac OS</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_System_requirements\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">System requirements</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Before you install, always make sure that your system meets the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/reader/system-requirements.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">minimum system requirements</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_1236799004\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h3 id=\"InstallingReaderonolderoperatingsystems\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">INSTALLING READER ON OLDER OPERATING SYSTEMS</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_1060360623\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If your operating system is older,</span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">you can install an earlier version of Reader. For step-by-step instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If you&rsquo;re not sure which version of Windows you have, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/which-operating-system\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Which Windows operating system am I running?</a></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_Internet_Explorer__Download_and_install_Adobe_Reader\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Explorer: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_1\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Internet Explorer.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step/step_par/image_692742472.img.jpg/get_adobe_reader_dc_windows.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the file download message appears at the bottom of the browser window, click <strong>Run</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Run\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step_2/step_par/img_0.img.png/security_warning.png\" alt=\"Click Run\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click <strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure/proc_par/step_4/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_1\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"main_Mozilla_Firefox__Download_and_install_Adobe_Reader\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Firefox: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_2\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Mozilla Firefox.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_458073859/step_par/image_1918909578.img.jpg/win10.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_458073859/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see&nbsp;<a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the Opening dialog box appears, click <strong>Save File</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Save File\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_2/step_par/img_0.img.png/save_file_dialog.png\" alt=\"Click Save File\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Press <strong>Ctrl+J</strong> to open the download Library. When the download Library window appears, double-click the .exe file for Reader.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Open the download Library\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_3/step_par/img_0.img.png/download_library1.png\" alt=\"Open the download Library\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If prompted to open the executable file, click <strong>OK</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to400\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click OK\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step_6/step_par/image_0.img.png/warning_message.png\" alt=\"Click OK\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_3\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"id_43756\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chrome: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_4\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Google Chrome.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image_1001882723.img.jpg/win10.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Click <strong>Save</strong> to download the Reader installer.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the downloaded file appears at the bottom of the browser window, click the .exe file for Reader.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_3/step_par/image.img.png/file_saved.png\" alt=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_5/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','2017-06-05 02:04:32','2017-08-02 05:51:47'),(23,1,1,'AirClass Update - AC Version 2.9','2017-06-28','<p>Hi teachers!<br /><br />51Talk is pleased to announce that AC version 2.9 is ready for launch. Upgrade will automatically commence once you login starting June 29, 2017. The upgrade would not interfere with any activity because download and update would happen in the background.<br /><br />The update contains IntelliSense which automatically checks the status of the microphone, speaker and network connection for both teacher and student. If any issue is&nbsp;detected during the class, IntelliSense will change into a red icon and teacher can click to expand and check on the problem.<br /><br />Recent bug fixes and improvements are also included in this new version.<br /><br />If you are on the old AC version, it is strongly advised that you logout of AC and reboot your device for the update to commence.</p>','2017-06-28 06:36:52','2017-06-28 06:36:52');
